\begin{frame}
    \frametitle{Conclusions}
    1. Loss of the IFN-\(\beta\)-IFNAR signalling pathway leads to production of Lewy Bodies, in the absence of any other mutations or overexpression\\
    \vspace{\baselineskip}
    2. IFN-\(\beta\) deficiency impairs autophagy, eventually leading to \(\alpha\)-synuclein aggregation\\
    \vspace{\baselineskip}
    3. IFN-\(\beta\) signalling normally acts to promote autophagy in neurons, clearing \(\alpha\)-synuclein\\
    \vspace{\baselineskip}
    4. Ifnb gene therapy appears to prevent much of the neurodegeneration associated with a familial PD model
\end{frame}

